Text.Value: I want something, yes. But I don't need you to be drawing breath in order to take it...
We hunt a weapon, taken from the ghaik slave ship. Have you seen such an item?
I have every right: I am strong, you are weak.
I gave you a chance to save your hide. Instead you chose empty bluster.
Don't be too hasty. I could prove very useful.
A worthless kill - no sport. If this one was even slightly useful, I might spare him...
A worthless kill - no sport. If this one was even slightly useful, I might spare her...
A worthless kill - no sport. If this one was even slightly useful, I might spare them...

EditorData.NodeContext: 'Voss' refers to Baretha's superior, who had recently chastised her lack of progress while the player observed from afar.

Text.Value: And if you come across any survivors of the ghaik vessel, kill them and search them. Thoroughly.
Your troubles are over; we shall help you. Baretha?
You may live. For the moment.
Lies. You speak like the vermin from this wretched world. What are you, a deserter?
I might know something. But it'll cost you.
Better to let stronger blood thrive. It can give rise to worthier foes and hardier slaves. Don't disappoint me.
You think you can worm your way into my head, simpleton?
Baretha! Rid us of this worm. I need to continue the hunt for the weapon.
I'll help if I can.
Attack.
I'll take your silence as respect, kin. But I would have you speak now...
Hmm. You make good use of silence. Too many think hot air will save them...
I don't know of such a weapon.
Baretha - keep hunting. And do better. Qudenos - we fly!
Kill him. Make it swift and clean.
Kill her. Make it swift and clean.
Kill them. Make it swift and clean.
...It is true. You were corrupted by the filthy spawn of the ghaik. Yet you still retrieved our queen's weapon.
If I have no use for you alive, I'll have your death, slow and sweet. Understand?
Impersonate a fierce gith and refuse him any explanation.
Of course you are not a threat! You are nothing until I tell you otherwise.
Ts'kva! You carry a ghaik parasite in your head! Death will be a kindness to you...
And in the company of local vermin...? Explain yourself, vin'iisk.
But there's a repellent logic in your words. You may notice things a noble gith does not.
Baretha! Rid us of this disgrace. I have to continue my hunt for the weapon.
These are local guides. I'll get rid of them once they cease to be useful.
The only value you hold is as meat to the carrion birds.
Do nothing.
Honestly? I'm not really a gith.
Silently hold his stare and discreetly prepare to attack.
No creature from this wretched world is important, half-wit.
I am no crèche hatchling. Do not speak to me as one.
Baretha! Kill this fiend. I will continue to hunt for the weapon elsewhere.
Help us find it and I will leave your blood beneath your skin, unspilled.
Tsk'va! You seek to impersonate us? To spy on us?
Show deference. Bow and explain that you are lost.
You have done well, in spite of your affliction. Allow me to reward you. Baretha?
Don't be foolish. I have powerful allies.
It is polyhedric in shape, inscribed with the sacred runes of our people. It is our queen's, and she shall have it back.
*You attune your mind to it. The artefact does not want to part from you. It does not want to fall into the gith raiders' hands.*
Say nothing.
At once... Htak'a!
We must not linger among such cattle. Even their warriors' blood shames our blades.
I need to know more. What is its appearance? Its purpose?
Did you not feel the devotion when inside my head? I could be an invaluable ally.
You must've seen my knowledge of these ancient lands. I could be of use to you.
You saw how ruthlessly I pursue my goals. I can help you.
A corpse is useless. But a living informant might unearth something.
A vessel fell from the sky. We seek a precious weapon that was taken from it.
Unlikely. But it costs me nothing to spare your sorry life.
Cunning. You will do well, vin'iisk.
It cannot be... You have the weapon? Someone would have reported it to me.
*You realise he's casting Detect Thoughts.*
Baretha! Kill this insolent worm. I need to continue my hunt.
*The gestures mean nothing to you - some sort of spell that you don't recognise.*
Curious. I thought even the lowest of creatures had at least a shred of dignity. You prove me wrong.
You'll need to start from the beginning - what is this weapon you're after?
Take them to the crèche. And see about fetching reinforcements. But first, a question...
*You attune your mind to it. The artefact does not want to part from you. It does not want to fall into the gith raiders' hands.*
Read his thoughts.
Pa'vrylk! You twist our noble words with a coward's tongue!
Baretha! Show this worm its place. I need to continue my hunt.
*He begins to move his hand in a quick flurry of gestures.*

These creatures are so simple to ensnare, Baretha. You mewl too much about your task.
Chk! You dare speak to me like my better? Others have died for lesser insults - slowly.

No matter. Baretha! This one is no kin to us. Kill him. I will continue searching for the weapon.
No matter. Baretha! This one is no kin to us. Kill her. I will continue searching for the weapon.
No matter. Baretha! This one is no kin to us. Kill them. I will continue searching for the weapon.
In gratitude, I'll grant you a swift death. Baretha? You know what to do.

Lie. Claim you saw bandits loot a wreck, then set off to the west.
You would've done so already if you didn't want something from me first.
Attack.
Senseless creature - I don't want to dull my blade on your overly thick skull.
Silently interpret the meaning of the gestures.

ROAR.

Synopsis: Our party encounters a band of githyanki warriors who have taken position at bottleneck in the region - a bridge that provides one of the few paths of progression. The gith confront us and try to see if we know anything about the 'weapon' they seek. (The weapon in question is the strange puzzle box we are carrying.) While reading our thoughts, the githyanki may realise we are tadpoled, resulting in instant combat. If we manage to conceal our tadpoles, they may allow us to pass.
